{{for|the [[subdistricts of Indonesia|subdistrict]] in [[Tuban Regency]], [[East Java]], [[Indonesia]]|Jenu (subdistrict)}}
In [[Mi'kmaq people|Mi'kmaq]] [[folklore]], a '''Jenu''' is a wild and [[cannibal]]istic hairy giant.

Jenua are comparable to the [[Wendigo]] of [[Anishinaabe]] and [[Cree]] [[mythology]] (and, to a lesser extent, [[Sasquatch]]).

