{{Infobox library | library_name = Kobe City Archives | library_logo = | image = Kobe-bunsyokan70.JPG | caption = Kobe City Archives building | location = [[Kobe]], [[Hyogo Prefecture]], [[Japan]] | established = 1938 | website = [http://www.city.kobe.lg.jp/information/institution/institution/document/index.html Kobe City Archives] }} The {{nihongo|'''Kobe City Archives'''|神戸市文書館|Kōbe-shi Bunshokan}} is the [[archive]] of the city of [[Kobe]] in [[Japan]].<ref>{{cite web | script-title=ja:地方公文書館について | url=http://www.cas.go.jp/jp/seisaku/koubun/dai5/siryou8.pdf | publisher=Cabinet Secretariat | accessdate=February 3, 2012|language=ja}}</ref> It contains records dating back to the mid 19th century. The building containing the archive is currently located in the [[Chūō-ku, Kobe|Chuo district]] of Kobe, near [[Shin-Kobe Station]]. The building is in [[Art Deco]] style, and was recognised as a "significant building" in 2000.
==Archived Items==
Archived items<ref>A full list of archived items can be found on the [http://www.city.kobe.lg.jp/information/institution/institution/document/top.html official website of the archives]</ref> include: * English language newspapers: ** ''The Hiogo and Osaka Herald'' (4 January 1868 to March 1870) ** ''The Hiogo News'' (23 April 1868 to 30 December 1887) ** ''The Kobe Chronicle'' (3 July 1897 to 31 December 1901) ** ''The Japan Chronicle'' (8 January 1902 to 26 December 1912) * Japan Gazette Official Directory from 1868 to the early 20th Century * Japanese Newspapers in the Archives include, ** ''Kobe Shinpo'' ** ''Kobe Nippo'' ** ''[[Kobe Shimbun]]'' ** ''[[Asahi Shimbun]] Hyogo Edition'' ** ''Shinko Hyogo Shinbun'' * Records from the [[Kobe foreign settlement]] and court records from that period (in both English and Japanese)
